Frankel fled the United States in May 1999.[8] He went by private plane to Rome and then to Hamburg, Germany,[6] where he was arrested on September 4.[1] He was first tried and sentenced in Germany to three years in jail for passport fraud. He was then extradited to the U.S. in 2001.[1]
