Executive Profile
Martin   Fraenkel  President of S&P Global Platts Inc, S&P Global Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 6 different industries.56--
Background

		Mr. Martin Fraenkel has been the President of S&P Global Platts Inc. (formerly, Platts, Inc.), a division of S&P Global, Inc. since September 29, 2016. Mr. Fraenkel served as Global Head of Content at S&P Global Platts Inc. since June 1, 2015 until September 29, 2016. He was responsible for managing the global editorial team, as well as for developing strategies for price assessments and analysis and all publications for the global commodities markets that Platts covers. ... He served as the Global Head of Energy at CME Group Inc since September 2014 and served as its Managing Director. He was responsible for developing and executing the strategy and product offering in the energy markets for the largest global exchange amid technological and regulatory changes. He also managed a global team that spanned London, Singapore, Houston, New York and Chicago. Mr. Fraenkel joined the CME Group Inc. in 2013 with more than 25 years of experience in global commodity markets. He held management roles in physical and financial markets. He served as an Executive Officer of Fixed Income Markets at Crédit Agricole Corporate and Investment Bank S.A. Over the course of his 30-year career at companies including Credit Agricole Corporate and Investment Bank, Dresdner Kleinwort, JPMorgan Chase and Phibro, he has managed trading businesses, led strategic and business planning for acquisitions and joint ventures and built new business lines. Before joining CME as Managing Director/head of International Energy in 2013, Mr. Fraenkel served as Global Head of Commodities at Credit Agricole CIB, Global Head of Energy, Base Metals and Agriculture at JPMorgan Chase & Co. and Chairman of the London Gold Market Fixing Ltd., which operates the London Gold Fix, from 2002 to 2004. Prior to that, as the Founder of London International Commodities, a UK consultancy, he advised clients including NYSE-Euronext, Louis Dreyfus Commodities and Highland Consulting on acquisitions, strategic and new business planning; portfolio optimization; risk management and hedging strategies. Mr. Fraenkel served as Senior Consultant of Commodities and Derivatives at Man Investments AG. He served as Managing Director and Global Head of Commodities at Dresdner Kleinwort. He served as an Executive Director of N M Rothschild & Sons Limited. He started his career at Phibro in New York. Mr. Fraenkel earned a Bachelor's degree in philosophy, politics and economics from Balliol College, Oxford, a Master's degree in international affairs from the Johns Hopkins University's School of Advanced International Studies and an MBA with a specialization in Finance from Insead in France.Read Full Background




